item.title: my PLUS version of Tronxy X5SA 400 pro
item.description:
This is my PLUS version of the Tronxy X5SA-Pro 400. Almost all parts can be adapted to the smaller / larger brothers.

The X5SA pro is a reasonably good basis. You can't get a solid basis cheaper. But you still have to do a lot to get a good printer.

Goal of the conversion:

  • Completely enclosed, tightly possible for later heating
  • Direct drive
  • Water cooling
  • new firmware
  • new board
  • better Z drive
  • more stable
    and above all: better cables (suitable for drag chains)

Status 2022-01-27
Frame angle - tested and installed
Switch housing - tested and installed
Z-drive with one motor - tested and installed
On / off housing - tested and installed
Connector housing - tested and installed
Water expansion tank - should work as a further development from an older version that was installed
Cable tray holder - tested and installed
Holder for water installation - to come
Holder for hotend - design ok, not tested

I have installed parts in PETG

I uploaded the current Fusion File. who wants to...

have fun

item.title: Aqara door sensor case (MCCGQ11LM)
item.description:
I designed this case in Fusion 360 for an Aqara door sensor mainly to use it for projects where I use this sensor as a general purpose zigbee sensor and I prefer something a bit smaller.

There are 2 versions, one with a hole and one without it, and also included the Fusion 360 file.

The one with the whole was designed to fit a small wire connector, which makes it handy to plug something else in there, or just use it as a normal door sensor if needed.

You might want to reduce the size slightly when printing, as I made it a bit bigger than the board itself, as the initial plan was to have the wire from the bottom to the top through the side of the board and solder it where the reed switch is, so I needed a bit of room. I ended up soldering the wires to the D+ and - directly to the board.

Use supports for the hole version.

item.title: Shade Tech(SHD TECH)
item.description:
SHD Tech (pronounced “Shade Tech”) is a shorthand for "Strategic Homeland Division Technology".

One of the Strategic Homeland Division's biggest advantages in the field is its revolutionary smart technology. Linked together into an intelligent grid by the SHD global satellite network, SHD Tech provides high-value, real-time intelligence for Division agents engaged in field operations.

Developed either exclusively by the Division's Research & Development department or adapted from military or commercial technological prototypes, SHD Tech is actually a catch-all term for all proprietary assets and systems employed exclusively by the Division and its agents. These include some of the most innovative augmented reality (AR) systems ever developed for policing or military actions: pod launchers, turrets, seeker mines and portable stations, to name a few.

SHD Network is the agency's core technology. It links numerous dedicated assets directly controlled by the Division - drones and other unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs), AWACS airplanes, and telecom satellites - and piggybacks their output onto existing civil, commercial, and military networking structures (cellphone towers, WiFi hotspots, NASA and GPS radionavigation satellites, and so on) to create a seamless global web of connectivity and data.

This redundancy ensures the SHD Network's reliability in case of catastrophic emergency. This reliability is crucial: the network connects agents in the field to Division HQ and to strategic government decision makers.

item.title: 3D Mouse / Mouse Companion Version 2
item.description:
Like if you do. Comment for improvement.

Please go to Thing Files and download each part separately.

Improved version

I'm disappointed/frustrated at my 3D Connexion Mouse Explorer. I find myself still using my mouse for the translations. Therefore I'm making my own interpretation of what a 3D mouse should be.

Print:

  • Most parts don't need any -or very few- supports.

Materials:

  • Joystick module 5-pin KY 23 PS2 with the circuit board (geometry is provided).
  • 4x mini press buttons (6x6x4.3 momentary button, 4 pin).
  • 1 rotary encoder (5-pin Module EC11).
  • 25x 6mm ball bearing (airsoft?).
  • 2x M3x16mm bolt + nut.
  • Arduino Pro Micro.
  • 55mm diameter rubber pad.

Assembly:

  1. Check the pictures, they are worth 1000 words.
  2. 27-Jan-2022: Code is not done yet.

Known Issues and Planned Solutions:

  • I'm waiting for an Arduino Pro Nano to check if there is enough place in the base for it.
  • Idea: replace the 4 buttons on the base with linear potentiometers.
  • Temporary solution for the code: I'll declare it as a joystick through the Arduino app and configure the functions with Joystick Gremlin app.
  • Longer term solution: design my own circuit board and code.


Use the referral code STAR-TQTV-6RL5 to get 5000UEC when creating a new account for Star Citizen.

item.title: Headphone stand
item.description:
Warning read this before printing!
I designed this headphone stand to print on my ender 5 pro(220x220). The extension was planned to snap on to the arm of the mainplate, but it didn't work with Pla and my settings. I broke the arm while I tried to snap it on. Then I slided the extension on the arm and glued it on. If you want to built it to snap on, you can customize it yourself (use "headphonestand_for costomization"). You can choose an Infill patter as an design element. if you don't know how to do it watch this video "Print Faster on Your Ender 3 Style Printer Using Tricks in Cura" from CHEP . You need to print the mainplate with support.

item.title: Sovol 3D - DUAL Filmanet Dry Box Stand Off
item.description:
Due to the Heatplate in my DUAL Filament Dryer from Sovol 3D, I made a StandOff for the DryBox.

The StandOff has a 20 mm height, to make sure that the Dryer has enough clearance for ventilation.

Share your make, that makes me more happy as a Tip.

Da mein DUAL Sovol 3D Filamenttrockner zu viel wärme abstrahlt (50° können auf dauer echt warm sein, vor allem für die Fläche wo die DryBox drauf steht), habe ich kurzer Hand einen Abstandshalter gebaut.

Mit einen abstand von 20mm zur Box, gibt es jetzt genügend platz zum Lüften.

Teile dein "make" mit mir, das würde mich sogar mehr freuen als ein Trinkgeld!

item.title: Y Stepper motor Cooler Ender 3 V2
item.description:
Redesigned from as the insulation from my print bed hits the housing, knocks it loose and adds resistance to the Y axis motor when the insulation runs over the top.

Trimmed down to fit under the insulation whilst still allowing airflow over and to the side of the stepper motor. Bolt holes line up with the internal screws on the factory 42mm by 34mm stepper motors. I have used my old hotend fan which was a 4010 fan though as stated on the original thing, a 4020 is also a good choice.

Will be looking to add cooling veins through the mounting flange in the future to allow some airflow to pass the face.
